title: For Sale:  Garmin eTrex Vista H Handheld GPS Navigator
postcontent:
Ideal for serious hikers and climbers, the rugged eTrex Vista H is an affordable, high performance GPS handheld featuring a high-sensitivity GPS receiver, detailed built-in basemap, USB interface (faster downloads), and 24MB of internal memory. In addition, the compact eTrex Vista H includes an electronic compass for continuous bearing information and a barometric altimeter for precise altitude. Put the great outdoors in the palm of your hand.
Pinpoint Your Location--and Direction
The Vista H's barometric altimeter pinpoints your precise altitude, and its built-in electronic compass provides bearing information even while you're standing still.

The Vista H can also receive position corrections from the Wide Area Augmentation System (WAAS), which makes its already-accurate positioning data even more reliable. In fact, when you turn on WAAS, you can increase the accuracy of Vista H's position reporting to within three meters. The device's high sensitivity means peak performance in any environment, from heavy foliage to deep canyons.

Add More Detail
The Vista H's basemap contains lakes, rivers, cities, interstates, national and state highways, railroads, coastlines, and landmarks. It also comes preloaded with marine navigation aids. And, with 24 MB of memory, you can add even more map detail with data from Garmin's entire line of MapSource mapping products (add maps in a snap with the high-speed USB connection).

24 MB is also plenty of room for waypoints, routes and saved tracks. The Vista H's automatic track log saves up to 10 tracks for retracing your path, and stores 20 routes with up to 125 waypoints per route.

See More Detail
With a high-contrast, backlit 2.4-inch LCD display, and 64 x 128 pixel resolution, you'll have no problem seeing your maps. The Vista H is compatible with mapping software including topographic maps, Bluechart and inland lake maps. It also includes built-in celestial tables for best times to hunt and fish.

Handheld Performer
The Vista H is engineered for comfortable, efficient handheld use. With its slim form factor, and weighing in at only 5.3 ounces with batteries, the Vista H is ready to go wherever you might take it. The four-way cursor provides smooth, one-hand operation, allowing you to move through menus and screens with ease. The rugged waterproof case (IPX7) gives you added protection against the elements, and a pair of AA batteries gets you up to 17 hours of use.

title: For Sale:  Once Fired Lake City .223/5.56 Brass (100% Processed)
postcontent:
I have 1000 pieces of once fired Lake City .223/5.56 brass for sale.  This brass has been fully processed by myself and is 100% ready for reloading.

My processing process consists of the following:

1. Is a 2 hour tumble in my Dillon CV-2001 tumbler in pretreated corn cob media to remove dirt and grime.   

2. I personally physically inspecting the head stamp of every piece and separating out everything but Lake City brass (it all appears to be from years 06 & 07).  

3. I physically inspect it for unusable defects, this brass is free of defects that would make it unusable and there is not a piece of it that I would not personally reload and use myself (brass may have some small marks or discolorations on it from being once fired and the fact that it is range brass).  

4. I run it through my Dillon 650XL press which deprimes the brass in the 1st station, 2nd station is the trim die where the brass is trimmed to 1.755 OAL (+/- .003) and full length case sized in the trim die, 3rd station it is run through my Dillon size die and once again is full length case sized and neck sized.

5. Each piece of brass is run through my Dillon Super Swage 600 where every piece of it had to be swaged, so I know that every piece of it is truly once fired brass.

6. Once again I tumble the brass in a water and stainless steel media bath for 3 hours in my Frankford Arsenal tumbler to clean the lube off the brass, clean the inside of the brass and primer pockets.

7. Each piece of brass has the case mouth deburred and I make sure that the inside of the casing is free of any tumbling media.

Lastly brass is separated into lots of 100 pieces and Ziploc bagged. 

Also, as I am not infallible I have included an extra 50 pieces of brass to cover any casings that might have defects in them that I might have missed.  The grand total of 1050 ready to load Lake City .223/5.56 brass casings can be yours for $120.00.  

Thanks for looking!
